> 7. Survivor‚Äôs Guilt in the Civilized Shell
When one ascends from hardship into relative peace, there may be an invisible reckoning: Why do I deserve this?
The subconscious, unable to rectify the injustice of others‚Äô continued suffering, induces unease as a form of psychic balancing. It
manifests not out of ungratefulness, but as a twisted sense of loyalty to those still suffering.
‚ÄúIf I cannot save them, I shall not be allowed to fully enjoy this.‚Äù
